[1] Colombia ex Venezuela
Date: Fri 22 Jun 2018, 4:22 PM
Source: RCN Radio [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.rcnradio.com/salud/casos-de-sarampion-importados-en-colombia-se-elevo-29


The National Institute of Health is evaluating 2567 suspected cases of measles and 384 suspected cases of rubella that have infected Colombians and visitors.

The Ministry of Health also confirmed that there are 29 cases of measles and 18 rubella in Colombia, the vast majority of them imported from people from Venezuela.

The cases studied of measles since [3 Mar 2018] to date [22 Jun 2018], have been identified in departments and cities such as Antioquia, Bolívar, Cartagena, Cauca, Cesar, Norte of Santander, Risaralda, Santa Marta, Sucre and Bogotá.

The health authorities revealed in the epidemiological bulletin that there are 7 cases of 2ary transmission of Venezuelans residing in Colombia for more than 4 months, without a clear vaccination report.

The health surveillance system added that 2 cases in Venezuelan citizens are also being monitored because of the evolution of the disease.

[Byline: Diana Cabrera]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The impact of the poor economic situation in Venezuela has had repercussions in healthcare including lapses in vaccination for vaccine-preventable diseases. This has fueled measles transmission in countries where Venezuelans have migrated.

The World Health Organization Measles and Rubella Laboratory Network (LabNet) provides for standardized testing in 183 countries and supports genetic characterization of currently circulating strains of measles viruses. Sequence information has proven to be extremely useful for tracking global transmission patterns. The WHO currently recognizes 8 clades of measles virus with at least 23 genotypes. This diversity aids in tracking movement of the virus.

A Healthmap of Colombia can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5876101,16 and of Venezuela at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5876101,29 - Mod.LK]

