[4] Serbia
Date: Sat 23 Jun 2018
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/serbia-measles-update-33-percent-patients-hospitalized-86969/


The Institute of Public Health of Serbia reported this week on the measles situation in the country. From October [2017] through [21 Jun 2018], 5598 measles cases were recorded, of which 2837 were laboratory confirmed at the Torlak Institute.

During this time, 15 measles related deaths were registered. As many as 33 percent of the patients required hospitalization because of the complications associated with measles; 565 people had pneumonia and 2 cases of encephalitis.

The majority of patients are in age groups younger than 5 and over 30 years of age, and 95 percent of those infected were either unvaccinated, incomplete vaccinated or unknown vaccine status.

[Byline: Robert Herriman]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
